Question: How can I read/write bits from/to a file in Java?: :I need to read file stream as bits and then I should be able to write bits to file again. Are there any classes for this purpose?
Please using this api: InputStream.read.
Answer:
<<<api>>>: InputStream.read
<<<code>>>:
public int read() throws IOException {
    if (pos >= count)
        return -1;
    return buf[pos++] & 0xff;
}
<<<explanation>>>:
This method reads the next byte of data from the input stream. The value byte is returned as an int in the range 0 to 255. If no byte is available because the end of the stream has been reached, the value -1 is returned. This method blocks until input data is available, the end of the stream is detected, or an exception is thrown.

A: You can use the BitInputStream and BitOutputStream classes from the Apache Commons IO library.
